run with: "make run"
then visit http://localhost:8080

accepted commands:
{"command":"invite", "data":{"id":"id1","group":"group1","ip":"ip1"}}
{"command":"login", "data":{"id":"id1","ip":"ip1"}}
{"command":"send", "data":{"id":"id1","message":"group1"}}

Included Ip as a security message, however, a better way might be that the node server
vill generate a new id for the user not the one linkedin returns, 
to minimize sniffing security concernes.